dct_title_s: Map of the Territory of Wisconsin
dct_description_sm: To accompany the Hon. Z. Casey's report.; Longitude referenced from Greenwich and Washington.; Shows Wisconsin Territory at greatest extent, including present-day states of Wisconsin, Minnesota, Iowa, and parts of North and South Dakota. Map also includes northern Illinois.; Indicates Indian tribal regions, land cessions and General Land Office districts.
